    "summary": "During my PhD research at the Farming Systems Ecology group I looked at ways to sustainably redesign smallholder farming systems in Northern India. I am interested in farmers\u2019 objectives and constraints and based on this I model how changes in farm management influence their livelihoods. Point of departure is the cohesion between systems-components soil, crops, animals, manure and the household.\nMy drive to understand processes and systems is not limited to farming systems. My interdisciplinary education makes me see human as part of bigger systems with drivers and challenges.",
