        {
            "title": "Crop Residue Project",
            "date": {
                "start": {
                    "month": 10,
                    "day": null,
                    "year": 2014
                },
                "end": {
                    "month": 10,
                    "day": null,
                    "year": 2014
                }
            },
            "description": "In collaboration with FAO (UN), the by FSE developed whole-farm model Farm DESIGN was adjusted to enable the calculation of energy production from crop residues and manures. \n\nAnaerobic digestion from crop and animal residues and by-products could be an attractive technology in particular for smallholders in the tropics. Different energy technologies are available to generate energy from these products: combustion, gasification, pyrolysis and anaerobic digestion. Among them anaerobic digestion (fermentation) is the main common technology used on-farm. With the adjusted model, the consequences of anaerobic combustion, and of the potential trade-offs involved in the use of crop products and manures for energy production can be explored. ",
